# ðŸ–¥ï¸ **Windows Performance Tune-Up Lab Guide**

## ðŸŽ¯ **Lab Overview**
This lab provides a step-by-step process to tune up and optimize a Windows computer without formatting. Students will learn how to improve system performance by removing unnecessary files, managing startup applications, and adjusting system settings.

## ðŸ“Œ **Objectives**
- **Learn how to perform basic daily maintenance.**
- **Apply weekly and monthly optimization techniques.**
- **Understand long-term performance improvement strategies.**

## ðŸ› ï¸ **Lab Tasks**

### âœ… **Daily Quick Maintenance**
- **Close unused apps and browser tabs.**
- **Open Task Manager (Ctrl + Shift + Esc). Check for unnecessary processes and end them.**
- **Save work and restart PC to refresh memory.**

### ðŸ”„ **Weekly Maintenance**
- **Delete temporary files:**
  - Press **Win + R â†’ type temp** â†’ delete contents.
  - Press **Win + R â†’ type %temp%** â†’ delete contents.
  - Run **Disk Cleanup**: Press **Win**, search for **Disk Cleanup**, and select the drive to clean.
- **Manage startup apps:**
  - Open **Task Manager â†’ Startup tab â†’ Disable non-essential apps.**
- **Update Windows & apps:**
  - Go to **Start â†’ Settings â†’ Update & Security â†’ Windows Update â†’ Check for updates.**
- **Run malware scan:**
  - Open **Windows Security â†’ Virus & Threat Protection â†’ Quick Scan.**

### ðŸ“… **Monthly Deep Tune-Up**
- **Optimize drives:**
  - Press **Win**, type **Defragment and Optimize Drives â†’ Select drive â†’ Optimize.**
  - For SSD, confirm TRIM is enabled: Open **Command Prompt â†’ run** `fsutil behavior query DisableDeleteNotify`. Value **0** means TRIM is enabled.
- **Clean large files:**
  - Open **File Explorer â†’ Downloads/Documents â†’ Move old files to external drive or cloud.**
- **Update drivers:**
  - Press **Win + X â†’ Device Manager â†’ Right-click device â†’ Update driver.**
- **Adjust performance settings:**
  - Press **Win + R â†’ type sysdm.cpl â†’ Advanced tab â†’ Performance Settings â†’ Adjust for best performance or leave default.**
- **Manage background apps:**
  - Go to **Settings â†’ Apps â†’ Installed Apps â†’ Modify background permissions.**

### ðŸ—“ï¸ **Every 6 Months**
- **Clean physical hardware:**
  - Power down PC, clean dust from fans and vents.
- **Full malware scan:**
  - Open **Windows Security â†’ Virus & Threat Protection â†’ Full Scan.**
- **Review installed software:**
  - Go to **Settings â†’ Apps â†’ Uninstall unused applications.**

## âš¡ **Bonus (Optional Upgrades)**
- **Add more RAM** if system usage stays above 80%.
- **Replace HDD with SSD** for significant speed boost.
- **Use Windows Reset (without deleting files)** if issues persist.

## ðŸ“‹ **Windows Performance Tune-Up Checklist**

### âœ… **Daily (Quick Habits)**
- [ ] **Close unused apps and browser tabs.**
- [ ] **Check Task Manager (Ctrl + Shift + Esc) if PC feels slow â†’ end unneeded processes.**
- [ ] **Save work and restart PC once a day (refreshes memory).**

### ðŸ”„ **Weekly (Light Maintenance)**
- [ ] **Delete temporary files:**
  - Run **Win + R â†’ temp** and **%temp%** â†’ delete contents.
  - Use **Storage Sense** or **cleanmgr.**
- [ ] **Check startup apps:** **Task Manager â†’ Startup tab â†’ keep only essentials.**
- [ ] **Update Windows & apps:** **Settings â†’ Windows Update.**
- [ ] **Scan for malware:** Quick scan with **Windows Defender (or Malwarebytes).**

### ðŸ“… **Monthly (Deep Tune-Up)**
- [ ] **Disk optimization:**
  - HDD â†’ **Defragment & Optimize Drives.**
  - SSD â†’ Confirm TRIM is enabled (`fsutil behavior query DisableDeleteNotify` should return 0).
- [ ] **Clean large files:** Move old downloads, videos, backups to external drive/cloud.
- [ ] **Check drivers:** Update **GPU, chipset, and network drivers.**
- [ ] **Performance settings:** Verify **Power Plan = Balanced or High performance.**
- [ ] **Background apps:** **Settings â†’ Apps â†’ Installed Apps â†’ Background Permissions â†’ set to Never for unused apps.**

### ðŸ—“ï¸ **Every 6 Months**
- [ ] **Dust cleanup:** Physically clean fans/vents to prevent overheating.
- [ ] **Full virus/malware scan.**
- [ ] **Review installed software â†’ uninstall unused apps.**

### âš¡ **Bonus (When Needed)**
- **Add more RAM** if usage is always >80%.
- **Switch HDD â†’ SSD** for a huge speed upgrade.
- **Reset Windows (without deleting files)** if performance still lags after all tune-ups.

## ðŸ“‹ **Deliverables**
